Certainly! Below is a concise C# code snippet that generates a poem containing at least one metaphor and one simile:

```csharp
using System;

class PoemGenerator
{
    static void Main()
    {
        string[] lines = new string[]
        {
            "The moon is a lantern in the night,", // Metaphor
            "Guiding lost souls with its gentle light.",
            "As silent as a whisper in the breeze,", // Simile
            "It paints silver dreams on the midnight seas."
        };

        Console.WriteLine("Generated Poem:\n");
        foreach (var line in lines)
        {
            Console.WriteLine(line);
        }
    }
}
```

This code defines a simple poem with four lines, ensuring it includes both a metaphor ("The moon is a lantern in the night") and a simile ("As silent as a whisper in the breeze"). The poem is printed line by line to the console.
